/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*\
  column05_reactive_methylacetate / constant/thermoPackage

  methanol + aceticAcid are the two column feeds, methylAcetate + water the
  esterification products formed on the reactive stages.  This quaternary
  mixture is strongly non-ideal (two azeotropes involving methyl acetate),
  so a predictive UNIFAC liquid is essential --- Raoult would misplace the
  product split.  The vapour stays ideal: acetic-acid dimerisation is a
  known, deliberately unmodelled simplification (see the inline notes).
\*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

components      ( methanol  aceticAcid  methylAcetate  water );
activityModel   { model UNIFAC; }     // predictive (UNIQUAC reactive convergence is a solver TODO; pairs are in standard)
equationOfState { model idealGas; }    // ideal vapour (acetic-acid dimerisation not modelled)
